<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 12 at 3:11PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern Moore,
northeastern Montgomery, southeastern Randolph and southwestern
Chatham Counties through 345 PM EDT...
At 311 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Seagrove, or 8 miles south of North Carolina Zoo, moving east at 20
mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
North Carolina Zoo, Seagrove, Robbins, Steeds, Harpers Crossroads,
Highfalls and Coleridge.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
